                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been reading here a bit but this is my first post.  I'm a 56 level enchanter on the Nameless.  I always group with my husband, who's a druid.  We've mostly been duoing, but we love LDoN and I'm still trying to get the kinks out of my strategies there.
<br />

<br />
I tend to lean toward the "Pacify as little as possible, have the puller pull, and mez adds" approach to LDoN, though obviously pacify is helpful.  I also consistently use AOE mezzes, which I know many people here don't.  My take on it is that when I see a bunch of mobs jumping us I like to be able to back off, mez the whole mess at once, and then sort out and mez individuals.  Sometimes I do mez myself (MR about 130), about once every other adventure, I'd say.  When that happens it's nice to have my husband right there in the room on the other computer so I can tell him (OK, "bark at him" might be a more appropriate term when I'm stressed) to have an emergency heal ready when mez starts to wear off.
<br />

<br />
So then, my question:  I've noticed, in MM especially, that bitten victims have been jumping up and asking to join me, and once a trap went off inexplicably and wiped us all.  I've seen mentioned on other boards that AOE stuns will set off traps, so I've pulled them from my lineup.  My question is, will AOE mez also trigger traps?  If so, I need to come up with a new way of approaching my mezzing.
<br />

<br />
Columbyne</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
