                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I cant comment on if AoE Mezes set off traps since I have never used one (havent seen the need and never picked up my 16 version of it). Seems odd that it would set off traps; however, bitten victims are awakened by hitting them, so perhaps the mez is triggering that. This is the first time I have seen this mentioned. And Victims have veried reactions from wanting to serve as pet to triggering harmful traps. Since traps are triggered (ie, when you hit them), I can only think that mez can serve as a trigger same as whacking them.
<br />

<br />
But if your strat does need to alter since you are an AoE mezer, then there are 2 routes you can take. The first would be to not worry about how many are pulled and single target mez them as you can.
<br />

<br />
The other is to utilize pacify line, which seems the most popular method. Chanter can pre-pacify rooms and pull. This allows you to line up mobs for your group so that they can quickly move from one mob to the next. An alternate approach is to pre-pacify as normal, and have the tank pull when previous mob is below 20% health and the others finish it off.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=583742" target="_blank" class="postlink">Phreza Bum</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
