                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">--Sigh-- I was afraid that would be the answer.  AOE mez can be a crutch, and I agree that if I (or someone else...one group told me to stop because it made them nervous to see their chanter getting hit) jump ahead and pacify a bit I should be able to keep the pulls to two or three mobs.  I've just been slow to make the shift because I've never pacified much, and I haven't been thinking about the lack of good AOE mez in the higher levels.
<br />

<br />
The moment when I realized I loved my enchanter was in Netherbian Lair, when our puller came screaming up out of a tunnel yelling something like "AAAGHthere'sfouronmeI'mgonnadiediedie" and I whacked him with my first AOE mez.  Everything went still and everyone spun around for a while before realizing the crisis was averted.  "Ah," said the puller sheepishly, "I forgot there was an enchanter in the group."  I just hate to leave any mobs hammering on anybody for a moment longer than I have to.
<br />

<br />
Columbyne</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
