                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I stay away from chests til after the adventure's over, but a good way to deal with Bitten Victims and other 'could be a pet' mobs is to tash them.  It can be any non-damaging spell but when you do tash them don't have a pet.  If you tash them and they're a pet mob, they'll stand up and still have full health.  If you tash them and they're a trap, they'll run over to you and hit you sometimes, with a health of 1-3%.  Just mez them and mem blur and they'll stand there and not aggro again.  Snare works also if you have a ranger/druid with you and you have a pet.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
