                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After a few times I seen my group wipe to one of the casters using AE i forbit it on my adventures.   I tend to take the bossy borderline bitchy chanter when playing.   I ALWAYS pull.  I pacify the rooms and will always have one mob mezed in camp debuffed and slowed as I pull with Tash and slow after mez if there is no shammy in group.   Funny I see this approach as normal and much easier then the whole mez the adds bit, I have yet to run out of mana on a crawl this way, as I can time the pulls and adds and usualy run around 30-40 mana will slow down to get around 60m when i know Haste is due (GOD I love timers).  
<br />

<br />
I used to let anyone pull, AE Stun then pick off the adds with usualy 2-3 of the mez's i had mem'd then when either my AE or someone else's started setting off traps in the forms if chests, tree's, coffins, victims that were causing us to lose I said no more AE's on any of my dungen crawls.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-----BEGIN ENCHANTER CODE BLOCK----- 
